unifdef - selectively remove C preprocessor conditionals

Written by Tony Finch <dot@dotat.at> - http://dotat.at/prog/unifdef/


To build, type make.

To install, copy unifdef to your bin directory and unifdef.1 to your
man/man1 directory.

Pre-formatted documentation can be found in unifdef.txt


Non-portable dependencies:

This program requires the BSD strlcpy() and err.h functions, and
C99 stdbool.h.


Please send bug reports and patches to me. I will assume that any
contributions are under the two-clause BSD licence, as found at the
top of unifdef.c

